<h1 class="title">Aniket Khanal Annual Review 2026</h1>
<p>
<b>Student:</b> Aniket Khanal
<b>Date:</b> Feb 20th 2026
<b>Members present:</b> John Alison / Matteo Cremonesi / Manfred Paulini / Brian Batel
<b>Title of current research:</b> Seach for Di-Higgs production in the bbWW final state
</p>

<p>
<b>Summary of Progress Since last review:</b>
</p>

<p>
Aniket has two ideas to improve the current HH-&gt;bbWW analysis. The
first is to increase H-&gt;WW acceptance by going lower in jet transverse
momentum. He argued in his slides why this is a wise strategy as it
can nearly double signal acceptance, while providing a handle to
suppress the leading ttbar background. His second idea for improving
HH-&gt;bbWW is to develop data-driven corrections for the ttbar
background. This again is a sensible thing to do as the current
analysis requires the accurate modelling of the tails of the ttbar
process to 1 part in a million. Data-driven corrections can provide
confidence in the background model and flexibly adapt to any feature
mismodelled by the simulation.
</p>


<p>
<b>Summary of research plan and recommendations of the committee</b>
</p>

<p>
Aniket's plan is to continue pursuing both improvement with the CMS
and bbWW effort.
</p>

<p>
The committee was impressed by the clear presentation of his work and
future plans. The committee notes that Aniket is making good progress
and recommends he keep up the good work.
</p>

<p>
<b>Expected graduation date:</b>  Fall 2028
